1
00:00:30,447 --> 00:00:31,614
Inmate 1625!

2
00:00:32,198 --> 00:00:33,366
Hey! Get off him!

3
00:00:44,377 --> 00:00:45,545
Let's get you treated.

4
00:01:08,568 --> 00:01:10,360
The wound is quite deep.

5
00:01:10,361 --> 00:01:13,739
We'll have to keep an eye on him
as he continues his treatment.

6
00:01:13,740 --> 00:01:15,157
How is Min Ji-ung?

7
00:01:15,158 --> 00:01:18,160
He wasn't hurt.
We've separated him from the attacker.

8
00:01:18,161 --> 00:01:20,288
Notify me
once you've questioned the attacker.

9
00:01:32,092 --> 00:01:33,760
Ms. Choi

10
00:01:34,928 --> 00:01:37,597
was the only adult who was good to me.

11
00:01:39,265 --> 00:01:41,976
And to such a teacher, I...

12
00:01:46,356 --> 00:01:49,149
I will live with remorse
for the rest of my life

13
00:01:49,150 --> 00:01:51,111
and repent until I die.

14
00:01:52,237 --> 00:01:56,282
I will not live a single moment
of my life in peace.

15
00:01:58,618 --> 00:01:59,994
I'm sorry.

16
00:02:06,292 --> 00:02:07,794
I'm sorry.

17
00:02:08,503 --> 00:02:09,879
I'm sorry.

18
00:02:10,380 --> 00:02:12,257
I'm truly sorry.

19
00:02:12,757 --> 00:02:14,968
I'm sorry.

20
00:02:50,545 --> 00:02:51,880
<i>What are you, a saint?</i>

21
00:02:52,380 --> 00:02:55,300
You'd be a psychopath
if you didn't feel anything.

22
00:02:56,259 --> 00:02:57,509
What did I tell you?

23
00:02:57,510 --> 00:02:59,178
That you'd see Cho Gyu-cheol,

24
00:02:59,179 --> 00:03:03,141
and a fire would burn in your heart
and drive you crazy.

25
00:03:05,101 --> 00:03:07,478
It's a fire neither of us
can ever extinguish.

26
00:03:07,979 --> 00:03:09,730
I told you, you would have to decide.

27
00:03:09,731 --> 00:03:11,774
Whether to live as Ga-yun's fiancé

28
00:03:12,275 --> 00:03:13,985
or as an ERPB inspector.

29
00:03:19,407 --> 00:03:20,408
You did well.

30
00:03:21,868 --> 00:03:22,952
Well done.

31
00:03:23,912 --> 00:03:25,872
Is that all you have to say?

32
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:29,959
Do you want me to pat you on the head
and compliment you?

33
00:03:31,252 --> 00:03:32,295
Yes, please do.

34
00:03:33,338 --> 00:03:34,839
Get lost, you punk!

35
00:03:37,258 --> 00:03:38,426
Gosh.

36
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:41,763
Let's go out tonight for some soju.

37
00:03:44,974 --> 00:03:46,351
Why aren't you answering?

38
00:03:49,062 --> 00:03:52,857
Living as Choi Gang-seok's son-in-law
wasn't one of the options.

39
00:03:55,735 --> 00:03:57,111
Get out, you punk!

40
00:03:57,820 --> 00:03:58,821
You can walk!

41
00:03:59,322 --> 00:04:01,198
Come on, we're almost there.

42
00:04:01,199 --> 00:04:04,326
You never let anything go, do you? Jesus.

43
00:04:04,327 --> 00:04:07,829
All I'm saying is
that it wasn't one of the choices.

44
00:04:07,830 --> 00:04:09,874
- You're feeling guilty--
- But I admitted it!

45
00:04:12,543 --> 00:04:14,336
- You're here, sir.
- Hello, sir.

46
00:04:14,337 --> 00:04:15,754
Let's cut the greetings.

47
00:04:15,755 --> 00:04:17,589
How's the drug investigation going?

48
00:04:17,590 --> 00:04:20,384
We have officially requested cooperation
from the police,

49
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:22,469
and we're searching schools
for hidden drugs.

50
00:04:22,470 --> 00:04:25,389
The official urine-test request form
for every school

51
00:04:25,390 --> 00:04:27,849
has been uploaded
for the full-scale investigation.

52
00:04:27,850 --> 00:04:29,227
And the gambling case?

53
00:04:29,727 --> 00:04:31,979
We're tracking
the gambling site's IP address.

54
00:04:31,980 --> 00:04:34,731
We've set it up to track them
through the loan sharks.

55
00:04:34,732 --> 00:04:36,066
This case is also serious.

56
00:04:36,067 --> 00:04:37,484
- Minister!
- Keep on top of it.

57
00:04:37,485 --> 00:04:41,071
- Minister!
- Sir, you can't act like this here.

58
00:04:41,072 --> 00:04:43,073
- Minister!
- I said you can't do this.

59
00:04:43,074 --> 00:04:44,324
Please, Minister.

60
00:04:44,325 --> 00:04:48,120
You need to follow the procedure
to see the minister.

61
00:04:48,121 --> 00:04:50,664
Who cares about the procedure? Minister!

62
00:04:50,665 --> 00:04:52,625
- What's going on?
- Minister!

63
00:04:54,168 --> 00:04:55,962
Minister!

64
00:04:57,171 --> 00:05:00,008
Please just take a look at this.

65
00:05:03,219 --> 00:05:07,265
This is the damage report

66
00:05:07,849 --> 00:05:09,642
from my own investigation.

67
00:05:11,311 --> 00:05:12,478
And

68
00:05:13,604 --> 00:05:14,439
these are

69
00:05:15,523 --> 00:05:16,816
formal complaints.

70
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:18,317
Just a moment.

71
00:05:18,318 --> 00:05:19,736
One moment, please!

72
00:05:21,112 --> 00:05:23,280
And these are medical records.

73
00:05:23,281 --> 00:05:25,949
And this is... Just a moment.

74
00:05:25,950 --> 00:05:27,410
Where did it go?

75
00:05:29,662 --> 00:05:32,081
Please take a look at it.

76
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:35,877
Please!

77
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:37,961
Please have a seat.

78
00:05:37,962 --> 00:05:39,756
- Please have a seat.
- Here.

79
00:05:42,091 --> 00:05:42,925
Here you are.

80
00:05:43,718 --> 00:05:44,886
Thank you.

81
00:05:57,065 --> 00:06:00,777
I have no one to talk to about this,

82
00:06:01,527 --> 00:06:03,112
and no one will listen.

83
00:06:03,696 --> 00:06:07,617
And it's not as if my son is innocent.

84
00:06:08,409 --> 00:06:09,911
You came to the right place.

85
00:06:10,536 --> 00:06:11,913
How can I help you?

86
00:06:17,794 --> 00:06:19,170
My punk of a son...

87
00:06:21,381 --> 00:06:25,342
Our sales for the third quarter increased
by 18% compared to last year.

88
00:06:25,343 --> 00:06:26,968
Our operating profit margin also...

89
00:06:26,969 --> 00:06:27,886
Hello?

90
00:06:27,887 --> 00:06:29,847
<i>You took your fucking time to answer.</i>

91
00:06:30,807 --> 00:06:32,642
<i>You're Lee Jae-yun's father, right?</i>

92
00:06:33,142 --> 00:06:34,894
- Look.
- <i>Fucking answer me.</i>

93
00:06:35,395 --> 00:06:37,188
<i>I said answer me!</i>

94
00:06:37,688 --> 00:06:38,814
Who is this?

95
00:06:38,815 --> 00:06:40,982
<i>You don't need to know who I am.</i>

96
00:06:40,983 --> 00:06:43,069
<i>Just pay off your goddamn son's debt.</i>

97
00:06:48,032 --> 00:06:50,243
I played a game.

98
00:06:51,494 --> 00:06:52,577
A game?

99
00:06:52,578 --> 00:06:54,246
Did you buy in-game items?

100
00:06:54,247 --> 00:06:56,498
How much do you owe exactly?

101
00:06:56,499 --> 00:06:59,043
Is it about 100,000 or 200,000 won?

102
00:07:00,044 --> 00:07:01,336
We're asking you!

103
00:07:01,337 --> 00:07:03,047
How much is the debt?

104
00:07:06,092 --> 00:07:09,262
About 85 million won...

105
00:07:11,806 --> 00:07:12,640
What?

106
00:07:13,975 --> 00:07:15,559
Eighty-five million won?

107
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:16,727
Oh my God.

108
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:18,437
Wait.

109
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:20,522
What on earth did you do?

110
00:07:20,523 --> 00:07:22,525
What kind of game did you play?

111
00:07:48,259 --> 00:07:52,513
TEACH YOU A LESSON

112
00:07:54,432 --> 00:07:55,349
Jae-yun.

113
00:07:57,226 --> 00:07:58,436
Mom and Dad

114
00:07:59,562 --> 00:08:00,605
paid off your debt.

115
00:08:02,064 --> 00:08:03,899
Everyone makes mistakes.

116
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:06,110
You just can't make the same one again.

117
00:08:06,986 --> 00:08:09,071
I'm sure Jae-yun will do better now.

118
00:08:09,572 --> 00:08:12,492
What matters is that you learn from this...

119
00:08:14,660 --> 00:08:15,828
and never do it again.

120
00:08:21,626 --> 00:08:22,460
Let's eat.

121
00:08:23,669 --> 00:08:24,670
Why are you crying?

122
00:08:30,092 --> 00:08:31,219
Don't cry.

123
00:08:31,802 --> 00:08:32,637
Don't cry.

124
00:08:44,649 --> 00:08:47,527
50,000 WON SIGN-UP BONUS
SURPRISE COUPON, CLICK NOW

125
00:09:03,668 --> 00:09:08,005
VIP GAME ROOM
UNLIMITED BONUS EVENT FOR A LIMITED TIME

126
00:09:17,265 --> 00:09:18,140
You little punk!

127
00:09:18,766 --> 00:09:20,100
You punk!

128
00:09:20,101 --> 00:09:23,019
We only just paid off your debt,

129
00:09:23,020 --> 00:09:25,523
and you gamble again? You punk!

130
00:09:27,024 --> 00:09:30,027
- You little punk.
- Honey, please don't...

131
00:09:52,258 --> 00:09:54,302
Just read webtoons on this
when you're bored.

132
00:09:57,096 --> 00:09:58,180
I won't gamble.

133
00:09:59,056 --> 00:10:01,267
I'm going to read just one webtoon.

134
00:10:26,917 --> 00:10:28,251
It's all right.

135
00:10:28,252 --> 00:10:29,794
- Just a moment.
- Look.

136
00:10:29,795 --> 00:10:31,338
- Hold on.
- Your kid is in debt.

137
00:10:31,339 --> 00:10:33,966
That means you gotta pay it back.

138
00:10:36,302 --> 00:10:37,927
It's fine. Just stay seated!

139
00:10:37,928 --> 00:10:40,847
If your damn kid screws up,

140
00:10:40,848 --> 00:10:42,850
you take the beating for them.

141
00:10:48,397 --> 00:10:51,233
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

142
00:10:56,072 --> 00:10:57,198
I really need...

143
00:10:59,116 --> 00:11:01,452
my severance pay.

144
00:11:05,289 --> 00:11:06,331
<i>You see,</i>

145
00:11:06,332 --> 00:11:09,210
I've tried everything I could.

146
00:11:12,046 --> 00:11:17,635
I put him on impulse-control medication
prescribed by a neuropsychiatrist.

147
00:11:20,805 --> 00:11:22,848
I even went to see a shaman.

148
00:11:23,349 --> 00:11:26,267
I already reported it to the police
a long time ago.

149
00:11:26,268 --> 00:11:27,687
But they say

150
00:11:28,688 --> 00:11:30,522
they can't do anything.

151
00:11:30,523 --> 00:11:32,941
Even if you block
the gambling site's IP address,

152
00:11:32,942 --> 00:11:35,653
all they have to do
is switch to a new one.

153
00:11:36,404 --> 00:11:41,242
There were
so many damn reviews and approvals.

154
00:11:41,826 --> 00:11:47,707
It took me six months
to get this paperwork done.

155
00:11:49,583 --> 00:11:52,127
And all the while,
time just kept slipping by.

156
00:11:52,128 --> 00:11:53,921
Please take a look at this.

157
00:11:54,922 --> 00:11:58,384
My son ran away from home.

158
00:11:59,927 --> 00:12:01,595
I don't even know if he's alive.

159
00:12:03,764 --> 00:12:06,142
I wasn't sure how to deliver this to you.

160
00:12:06,767 --> 00:12:08,518
I'm sorry, Minister!

161
00:12:08,519 --> 00:12:11,730
I'm not sure
how I should give this to you.

162
00:12:11,731 --> 00:12:13,064
I'm sorry.

163
00:12:13,065 --> 00:12:15,025
You don't have to say

164
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:18,779
anything else to us.

165
00:12:24,243 --> 00:12:25,201
NAKWON HIGH SCHOOL

166
00:12:25,202 --> 00:12:26,369
<i>Everyone, say hello.</i>

167
00:12:26,370 --> 00:12:30,331
This is Bong Geun-dae, a new student
joining our class from today.

168
00:12:30,332 --> 00:12:31,250
Say hi.

169
00:12:32,251 --> 00:12:35,671
Hi, I'm Bong Geun-dae. I'm new here.

170
00:12:40,176 --> 00:12:42,720
Why don't you sit over there
in front of Seong-bin?

171
00:12:43,220 --> 00:12:45,848
Seong-bin,
have you heard from Jae-yun yet?

172
00:12:46,724 --> 00:12:48,975
- No.
- If you do, let me know right away.

173
00:12:48,976 --> 00:12:49,893
Okay.

174
00:12:49,894 --> 00:12:52,646
- Have a great day!
- Yes, ma'am!

175
00:12:56,108 --> 00:12:57,025
I won!

176
00:12:57,026 --> 00:12:58,151
I won again!

177
00:12:58,152 --> 00:12:59,319
How much did you win?

178
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:00,987
- One million won.
- Bull!

179
00:13:00,988 --> 00:13:02,656
Look. It's for real.

180
00:13:04,325 --> 00:13:05,493
Another jackpot!

181
00:13:09,872 --> 00:13:10,873
- Too bad.
- Damn it.

182
00:13:12,082 --> 00:13:14,043
Fucking hell!

183
00:13:14,752 --> 00:13:15,960
I'm so done.

184
00:13:15,961 --> 00:13:17,046
Yes, 200,000 won!

185
00:13:21,550 --> 00:13:24,929
Fuck, that was close.
My mom would've lost her shit.

186
00:13:25,805 --> 00:13:26,806
- What?
- What?

187
00:13:28,349 --> 00:13:30,433
Goddamn it!

188
00:13:30,434 --> 00:13:33,103
What the hell are you staring at, dumbass?

189
00:13:33,771 --> 00:13:38,067
<i>They say online gambling
wouldn't survive without teenagers.</i>

190
00:13:39,193 --> 00:13:44,405
Our recent online gambling busts showed
that over 50% of their users were minors.

191
00:13:44,406 --> 00:13:46,908
There was even a 9-year-old. A 9-year-old!

192
00:13:46,909 --> 00:13:50,954
Loan sharks are always
around kids who gamble.

193
00:13:50,955 --> 00:13:52,872
- There--
- A few million won is nothing.

194
00:13:52,873 --> 00:13:55,917
Those kids owe hundreds of millions!
They owe...

195
00:13:55,918 --> 00:13:57,502
There have also been many cases

196
00:13:57,503 --> 00:14:00,129
where kids, like Jae-yun,
have run away from home.

197
00:14:00,130 --> 00:14:01,506
Gambling is one thing,

198
00:14:01,507 --> 00:14:03,591
but the related crimes
are just as serious.

199
00:14:03,592 --> 00:14:05,593
Most of it is to pay off debts.

200
00:14:05,594 --> 00:14:07,929
We will catch these punks.

201
00:14:07,930 --> 00:14:11,891
But we can't do it alone.
We'll need help from other departments.

202
00:14:11,892 --> 00:14:14,519
They say it takes a village
to raise a child.

203
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:17,480
The police, prosecutors, the MSIT,
and the Ministry of Justice

204
00:14:17,481 --> 00:14:18,482
must all cooperate.

205
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:23,486
If they refuse to,
I'll have to drag them in by the collar.

206
00:14:23,487 --> 00:14:26,197
But I think they're all higher up
in the chain than us.

207
00:14:26,198 --> 00:14:28,117
The kids' card wins hands down.

208
00:14:30,703 --> 00:14:31,912
Good day, sir.

209
00:14:40,170 --> 00:14:41,088
Where were you at?

210
00:14:41,672 --> 00:14:43,965
I came straight from home.

211
00:14:43,966 --> 00:14:46,176
Dumbass. Not that. Which school?

212
00:14:47,219 --> 00:14:48,177
Guun High.

213
00:14:48,178 --> 00:14:50,096
I got it! Hell yeah!

214
00:14:50,097 --> 00:14:52,432
- What is it? Did you hit it big?
- Really?

215
00:14:52,433 --> 00:14:53,391
How much?

216
00:14:53,392 --> 00:14:54,893
Fuck, it's a million won.

217
00:14:54,894 --> 00:14:56,019
- A million.
- A million?

218
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:58,438
- You might actually buy a motorcycle.
- What is that?

219
00:14:58,439 --> 00:15:00,273
I won, so dinner's on me tonight.

220
00:15:00,274 --> 00:15:02,692
Hey! Anyone up for some good food?

221
00:15:02,693 --> 00:15:04,862
Fuck, Seong-bin is buying today!

222
00:15:06,030 --> 00:15:07,655
I hit the jackpot, suckers!

223
00:15:07,656 --> 00:15:09,282
I want octopus <i>jjamppong</i>!

224
00:15:09,283 --> 00:15:10,700
- Seafood for me!
- Beef for me.

225
00:15:10,701 --> 00:15:12,620
- Sure.
- I'll have braised pork belly!

226
00:15:14,413 --> 00:15:16,999
Maybe black bean noodles?

227
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:19,959
I'm all in on Banker until the run breaks.

228
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:21,252
Hey, hold on.

229
00:15:21,253 --> 00:15:24,172
Trust me, let's bet on "tie."
The streak's gonna break.

230
00:15:24,173 --> 00:15:26,925
Don't you know not to trust anyone
going for a tie?

231
00:15:26,926 --> 00:15:29,135
You mean full house, not tie, you idiot.

232
00:15:29,136 --> 00:15:30,429
The Banker is drawing.

233
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:43,066
What is it?

234
00:15:43,067 --> 00:15:44,484
Can you let me in too?

235
00:15:44,485 --> 00:15:45,945
I told you it's just a game.

236
00:15:46,528 --> 00:15:47,987
Isn't it like gambling?

237
00:15:47,988 --> 00:15:50,114
I saw you win money.

238
00:15:50,115 --> 00:15:51,658
Gambling is a scary thing.

239
00:15:51,659 --> 00:15:53,786
This is just a game. A money-making one.

240
00:15:54,536 --> 00:15:56,245
Don't you play with your own money?

241
00:15:56,246 --> 00:15:59,082
Who uses their own money?
You get a free bonus when you join.

242
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:03,836
Seong-bin here flipped the free bonus
and bought an RTX 5090 Ti graphics card.

243
00:16:03,837 --> 00:16:06,172
- An RTX 5090 Ti? That's super expensive.
- Yeah.

244
00:16:06,173 --> 00:16:07,132
You can do it too.

245
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:10,594
- Shall I show you?
- Yeah.

246
00:16:11,845 --> 00:16:12,887
If you sign up here

247
00:16:12,888 --> 00:16:15,766
and enter my ID for the referral,
you get an extra 50,000 won.

248
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:17,308
Just a moment.

249
00:16:17,309 --> 00:16:19,394
Do I really get free money?

250
00:16:19,395 --> 00:16:20,688
For God's sake!

251
00:16:22,815 --> 00:16:23,649
Give me that.

252
00:16:25,025 --> 00:16:27,485
First, sign up.

253
00:16:27,486 --> 00:16:29,570
Create your password.

254
00:16:29,571 --> 00:16:30,823
And for the code...

255
00:16:31,657 --> 00:16:32,865
Hey, see that?

256
00:16:32,866 --> 00:16:34,242
You got 50,000 won.

257
00:16:34,243 --> 00:16:36,829
Since you don't know anything,
start with Odd or Even.

258
00:16:37,413 --> 00:16:38,621
- Odd or Even?
- Hurry.

259
00:16:38,622 --> 00:16:39,539
- Just pick.
- Pick.

260
00:16:39,540 --> 00:16:40,957
I'll go with odd.

261
00:16:40,958 --> 00:16:42,126
- Tap on it.
- Right.

262
00:16:46,463 --> 00:16:48,047
- This guy got it.
- Let's see.

263
00:16:48,048 --> 00:16:49,257
You've got the touch.

264
00:16:49,258 --> 00:16:50,426
Even.

265
00:16:53,595 --> 00:16:55,097
<i>Hey, what the hell?</i>

266
00:16:55,597 --> 00:16:56,472
Here.

267
00:16:56,473 --> 00:16:59,600
This kid, who approached me first,
is the recruiter.

268
00:16:59,601 --> 00:17:02,437
He's Seong-bin,
and he works with a few shills.

269
00:17:02,438 --> 00:17:05,106
At first, they say they've won big,

270
00:17:05,107 --> 00:17:08,026
getting you curious and interested.

271
00:17:08,027 --> 00:17:10,445
Then they exclude you
from the conversation.

272
00:17:10,446 --> 00:17:13,740
And if you don't gamble,
they isolate you like an outcast.

273
00:17:13,741 --> 00:17:16,910
They say "game" instead of "gambling."
It's less off-putting.

274
00:17:17,494 --> 00:17:20,621
Is the next move
for Deputy Director Bong to lose money?

275
00:17:20,622 --> 00:17:23,249
But there's something I don't understand.

276
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:25,918
Gambling is basically math.

277
00:17:25,919 --> 00:17:28,004
If you know middle school math

278
00:17:28,005 --> 00:17:30,506
and know how to apply statistics,

279
00:17:30,507 --> 00:17:33,551
it's a system where you can't lose money.

280
00:17:33,552 --> 00:17:34,636
I see.

281
00:17:35,137 --> 00:17:35,970
Is that so?

282
00:17:35,971 --> 00:17:38,974
You don't have to lose money on purpose.
Win if you can.

283
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:42,769
Then what do I do with the money I win?

284
00:17:42,770 --> 00:17:44,438
It's yours as a bonus.

285
00:17:45,022 --> 00:17:46,355
Come on.

286
00:17:46,356 --> 00:17:47,733
You don't believe me.

287
00:17:48,317 --> 00:17:49,735
- Do you?
- Are you serious?

288
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:52,988
If you win it yourself, what can I say?

289
00:17:58,619 --> 00:17:59,995
All right.

290
00:18:05,250 --> 00:18:07,628
- The 5090 graphics card...
- Is that really allowed?

291
00:18:08,462 --> 00:18:10,255
Yeah, you'll see.

292
00:18:28,232 --> 00:18:30,024
<i>What do I do with the money I win?</i>

293
00:18:30,025 --> 00:18:35,864
<i>It's yours as a bonus.</i>

294
00:18:47,709 --> 00:18:48,794
ODD

295
00:19:14,236 --> 00:19:15,779
EVEN

296
00:19:19,366 --> 00:19:20,492
ODD

297
00:19:45,475 --> 00:19:48,312
YOUR BALANCE IS ZERO
RECHARGE

298
00:19:54,651 --> 00:19:56,028
What's up with this guy?

299
00:19:57,571 --> 00:20:00,240
You must have been at it all night.

300
00:20:00,741 --> 00:20:01,658
Did you win?

301
00:20:02,367 --> 00:20:03,367
I lost.

302
00:20:03,368 --> 00:20:04,411
How much?

303
00:20:05,871 --> 00:20:07,747
- A million.
- You crazy bastard.

304
00:20:07,748 --> 00:20:10,125
I told you to only use the bonus cash.

305
00:20:11,793 --> 00:20:14,588
Are you going to do anything? Win it back?

306
00:20:15,797 --> 00:20:16,965
How do I win it back?

307
00:20:18,217 --> 00:20:20,677
You know Martingale's
miraculous betting strategy?

308
00:20:21,595 --> 00:20:25,057
My good friend Martingale
invented a method where you can't lose.

309
00:20:26,183 --> 00:20:28,977
You double your bet every time you lose.

310
00:20:29,561 --> 00:20:31,355
If you lose 100 won, you bet 200 won.

311
00:20:31,855 --> 00:20:34,524
If you lose 200 won? 400 won.
If you lose 400 won?

312
00:20:35,108 --> 00:20:36,902
- 800 won?
- That's right.

313
00:20:37,402 --> 00:20:40,238
You're bound to win eventually.
We just need to win once.

314
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:43,157
You're right.
If you win just once, you break even.

315
00:20:43,158 --> 00:20:44,075
Exactly.

316
00:20:44,076 --> 00:20:47,829
It's an insane, unbeatable method.
You can't lose as long as you have money.

317
00:20:49,706 --> 00:20:51,750
I'm the king of connections around here.

318
00:20:52,751 --> 00:20:54,544
I know a guy who can lend you money.

319
00:20:55,712 --> 00:20:56,630
Do you want some?

320
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:00,592
What's there to think about, man?

321
00:21:02,010 --> 00:21:03,219
Hello.

322
00:21:03,220 --> 00:21:05,305
I've got a friend who needs some cash.

323
00:21:06,014 --> 00:21:07,474
Yes, about a million won?

324
00:21:08,850 --> 00:21:11,561
He says he'll lend it to you,
but he needs some collateral.

325
00:21:12,145 --> 00:21:13,396
- Collateral?
- Nothing big.

326
00:21:13,397 --> 00:21:15,898
- Just your parents' numbers.
- My parents' numbers?

327
00:21:15,899 --> 00:21:17,483
It's just a formality.

328
00:21:17,484 --> 00:21:20,279
We're not going to lose anyway.
Martingale, remember?

329
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:29,745
But didn't you say it was a million won?

330
00:21:29,746 --> 00:21:31,539
I only received 800,000 won.

331
00:21:31,540 --> 00:21:33,291
Upfront interest, dumbass.

332
00:21:33,292 --> 00:21:35,585
He takes 20% and gives you the rest.

333
00:21:39,214 --> 00:21:41,048
The interest rate is 3% per day.

334
00:21:41,049 --> 00:21:43,050
For 1,000,000 won, 3% is 30,000 won.

335
00:21:43,051 --> 00:21:48,264
The next day, it's not 3% of 1,000,000 won
but 3% of 1,030,000 won after interest.

336
00:21:48,265 --> 00:21:50,309
It's calculated as compound interest.

337
00:21:51,184 --> 00:21:52,436
After a month,

338
00:21:52,936 --> 00:21:56,898
800,000 won becomes 2,427,243 won.

339
00:21:57,733 --> 00:22:02,362
And after 100 days,
it becomes 19,218,364 won.

340
00:22:04,197 --> 00:22:09,077
After a year,
it becomes 48,482,008,003 won.

341
00:22:09,911 --> 00:22:11,162
You did well. Okay?

342
00:22:11,163 --> 00:22:13,164
Good job. Well done.

343
00:22:13,165 --> 00:22:18,920
Deputy Bong, my man. You lost big time,
so they'll come down on you soon.

344
00:22:19,671 --> 00:22:20,922
Don't cry.

345
00:22:26,219 --> 00:22:27,054
Hello?

346
00:22:27,554 --> 00:22:28,930
<i>Are you Bong Geun-dae's mom?</i>

347
00:22:29,639 --> 00:22:31,099
- What?
<i>- Answer me, damn it!</i>

348
00:22:32,059 --> 00:22:34,643
Watch your mouth.
Why would I be Bong Geun-dae's mom?

349
00:22:34,644 --> 00:22:36,228
Geun-dae's mom, who is it?

350
00:22:36,229 --> 00:22:38,398
- My mom?
- Be quiet! She's on the phone.

351
00:22:41,193 --> 00:22:43,152
Yes, I'm Geun-dae's mom.

352
00:22:43,153 --> 00:22:45,405
<i>You need to pay off your son's debt.</i>

353
00:22:46,198 --> 00:22:47,823
Did my son gamble again?

354
00:22:47,824 --> 00:22:48,991
How much this time?

355
00:22:48,992 --> 00:22:51,495
<i>The kid plays on a fucking grand scale.
20 million.</i>

356
00:22:54,039 --> 00:22:57,041
<i>- Hey, lady. Pay me back fast.</i>
- You did well.

357
00:22:57,042 --> 00:22:59,252
<i>The interest alone
will be 600,000 won tomorrow.</i>

358
00:22:59,753 --> 00:23:03,256
I can't pay it back.
I've paid his debts time and again.

359
00:23:03,924 --> 00:23:06,842
Trying to save this fool
will destroy my family.

360
00:23:06,843 --> 00:23:10,055
I've given up on Geun-dae.
Do as you wish. Kill him or don't.

361
00:23:10,722 --> 00:23:11,765
Damn it.

362
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:15,101
He's calling me again.

363
00:23:15,102 --> 00:23:16,520
Again! For God's sake.

364
00:23:18,480 --> 00:23:19,438
What do we do now?

365
00:23:19,439 --> 00:23:21,524
These recruiters
are probably just small fry.

366
00:23:21,525 --> 00:23:23,109
Operations like this run on cash.

367
00:23:23,110 --> 00:23:25,987
The guys actually handling the money
know who's at the top.

368
00:23:28,115 --> 00:23:30,908
Our Deputy Bong lost big time, right?

369
00:23:30,909 --> 00:23:32,993
So they'll have the enforcers
come after you.

370
00:23:32,994 --> 00:23:34,538
We catch those guys

371
00:23:35,664 --> 00:23:38,917
and take down... those at the top.

372
00:23:41,128 --> 00:23:42,963
Come on, don't cry.

373
00:23:43,463 --> 00:23:44,297
Okay.

374
00:23:45,340 --> 00:23:47,426
NAKWON HIGH SCHOOL

375
00:23:50,929 --> 00:23:54,724
<i>There's no sign of the enforcers.
You're watching me closely, right?</i>

376
00:23:56,393 --> 00:23:58,812
<i>I'm close by, watching over you.</i>

377
00:24:07,112 --> 00:24:07,945
Damn it.

378
00:24:07,946 --> 00:24:10,282
I picked the wrong spot.

379
00:24:14,327 --> 00:24:16,288
DELICIOUS GIMBAP, TTEOKBOKKI,
TWIGIM, SUNDAE

380
00:24:32,220 --> 00:24:33,971
- Hello!
- Hi, welcome.

381
00:24:33,972 --> 00:24:36,182
- Just one portion, please.
- Order more.

382
00:24:36,183 --> 00:24:38,767
- Come on, here. I'll give you lots.
- Damn.

383
00:24:38,768 --> 00:24:40,978
That's awesome. Thank you.

384
00:24:40,979 --> 00:24:42,105
Enjoy.

385
00:24:43,064 --> 00:24:43,981
Thank you.

386
00:24:43,982 --> 00:24:45,649
- How sweet.
- It looks so good.

387
00:24:45,650 --> 00:24:47,485
- Enjoy.
- We will. Thank you.

388
00:24:47,486 --> 00:24:49,570
Ma'am, can I please get one <i>tteokbokki</i>?

389
00:24:49,571 --> 00:24:50,738
All right.

390
00:24:50,739 --> 00:24:52,781
- Please mix in some <i>twigim.</i>
- Here you go.

391
00:24:52,782 --> 00:24:55,785
- Thank you.
- Sure, please enjoy.

392
00:25:22,771 --> 00:25:24,940
Unlock your phones and hand them over.

393
00:25:28,193 --> 00:25:29,402
Hurry up!

394
00:25:31,404 --> 00:25:33,448
Hurry up and hand them over.

395
00:25:34,407 --> 00:25:35,616
Hurry up.

396
00:25:35,617 --> 00:25:38,119
Just fucking hand them over!

397
00:25:41,164 --> 00:25:42,165
Hey.

398
00:25:42,666 --> 00:25:43,708
I said hand it over.

399
00:25:44,501 --> 00:25:46,961
It's the fingerprint recognition.

400
00:25:46,962 --> 00:25:48,838
- It's not working.
- Give it here.

401
00:25:56,513 --> 00:25:57,513
- Oh no.
- Damn it.

402
00:25:57,514 --> 00:25:59,139
- I'm sorry.
- Fucking hell.

403
00:25:59,140 --> 00:26:00,350
For fuck's sake.

404
00:26:00,850 --> 00:26:02,102
Oh no.

405
00:26:02,602 --> 00:26:03,979
My phone

406
00:26:05,105 --> 00:26:06,981
fell into the sewer.

407
00:26:06,982 --> 00:26:10,277
For fuck's sake.
You're a real piece of work.

408
00:26:10,860 --> 00:26:12,320
I'm sorry.

409
00:26:23,290 --> 00:26:27,793
INSPECTOR IM HAN-RIM

410
00:26:27,794 --> 00:26:29,878
I definitely saw him make it this far.

411
00:26:29,879 --> 00:26:32,381
I watched him from over there,
making eye contact.

412
00:26:32,382 --> 00:26:34,758
- <i>The call cannot be connected.</i>
- He's not answering.

413
00:26:34,759 --> 00:26:36,970
Get that CCTV footage. Let's go.

414
00:26:39,973 --> 00:26:42,767
My money!

415
00:26:43,435 --> 00:26:46,021
Pay me back, or you're all fucking dead.

416
00:26:46,521 --> 00:26:48,480
Your parents won't pay your debts anymore.

417
00:26:48,481 --> 00:26:51,067
You'll have to earn the money
to pay me back.

418
00:26:51,776 --> 00:26:53,069
Take this. Take it.

419
00:26:55,071 --> 00:26:57,741
Go empty the ice cream shop's cash box.

420
00:26:58,700 --> 00:26:59,868
Move it!

421
00:27:24,225 --> 00:27:25,268
Good.

422
00:27:29,356 --> 00:27:30,190
Good job.

423
00:27:30,940 --> 00:27:31,775
Get in.

424
00:27:39,240 --> 00:27:40,450
If you don't do it,

425
00:27:41,368 --> 00:27:42,660
you'll be dead.

426
00:27:42,661 --> 00:27:44,037
You get what I'm saying?

427
00:27:44,829 --> 00:27:47,040
- Why are you--
- Hold it. I said hold it properly.

428
00:27:48,875 --> 00:27:50,209
- No, I can't.
- Get out, moron.

429
00:27:50,210 --> 00:27:51,377
- I can't.
- Get out.

430
00:27:51,378 --> 00:27:53,087
- Get the fuck out.
- I really can't.

431
00:27:53,088 --> 00:27:55,631
- I said get the fuck out.
- No, I really can't do it.

432
00:27:55,632 --> 00:27:57,467
For fuck's sake.

433
00:28:07,560 --> 00:28:08,687
- You little shit.
- What...

434
00:28:09,562 --> 00:28:10,980
Do you know who I am, moron?

435
00:28:11,564 --> 00:28:12,439
- Hey!
- What the...

436
00:28:12,440 --> 00:28:13,357
- I'm scared.
- Hey!

437
00:28:13,358 --> 00:28:15,443
Sir, are you all right? Get it together.

438
00:28:28,998 --> 00:28:29,833
Shit.

439
00:28:32,293 --> 00:28:33,502
Run the plate

440
00:28:33,503 --> 00:28:36,046
and track the vehicle on the CCTV.

441
00:28:36,047 --> 00:28:38,674
I'll go to traffic control
and get their cooperation.

442
00:28:38,675 --> 00:28:39,592
Yes, sir.

443
00:28:44,764 --> 00:28:45,889
We don't have time.

444
00:28:45,890 --> 00:28:47,182
Get your head together.

445
00:28:47,183 --> 00:28:48,852
It's all my fault.

446
00:28:50,061 --> 00:28:53,314
I lost Deputy Director Bong
because of that fucking <i>tteokbokki</i>!

447
00:28:53,815 --> 00:28:56,568
What if something happens to him
because of me?

448
00:28:58,570 --> 00:29:00,195
Sergeant Im Han-rim!

449
00:29:00,196 --> 00:29:01,990
That's right, Sergeant Im Han-rim.

450
00:29:03,700 --> 00:29:05,785
You can make up for mistakes,

451
00:29:07,370 --> 00:29:09,038
but giving up is failure.

452
00:29:11,541 --> 00:29:12,417
Understood?

453
00:29:13,418 --> 00:29:14,711
Yes, sir. Understood!

454
00:29:18,590 --> 00:29:19,507
Get moving.

455
00:29:25,472 --> 00:29:26,305
What the hell?

456
00:29:26,306 --> 00:29:27,765
Where did all the morons go?

457
00:29:27,766 --> 00:29:29,892
Seriously, for fuck's sake.

458
00:29:29,893 --> 00:29:31,602
Fucking hell. Hey!

459
00:29:31,603 --> 00:29:33,271
I told you to close your eyes.

460
00:29:43,156 --> 00:29:44,324
Don't push me.

461
00:29:45,325 --> 00:29:46,658
Wait a moment.

462
00:29:46,659 --> 00:29:48,160
- Wait.
- Hello, boss!

463
00:29:48,161 --> 00:29:50,913
You fucking bastards.
Really? You're eating now?

464
00:29:50,914 --> 00:29:52,039
I'm sorry, bro.

465
00:29:52,040 --> 00:29:53,791
Do I have to deal with kids myself?

466
00:29:53,792 --> 00:29:55,168
- Damn it.
- I'm sorry!

467
00:29:56,211 --> 00:29:58,254
- Get your act together.
- Yes, bro!

468
00:29:59,130 --> 00:30:01,215
Fucking morons.

469
00:30:01,216 --> 00:30:02,884
- Good night.
- Good night.

470
00:30:03,718 --> 00:30:05,219
This moron is a newbie.

471
00:30:05,220 --> 00:30:06,970
Train him and get him started.

472
00:30:06,971 --> 00:30:08,515
Yes, bro!

473
00:30:09,933 --> 00:30:11,267
Fucking follow me.

474
00:30:12,393 --> 00:30:14,978
That's my bag.

475
00:30:14,979 --> 00:30:17,398
- For fuck's sake. Come with me.
- Wait...

476
00:30:23,947 --> 00:30:25,072
- Sit.
- Sorry?

477
00:30:25,073 --> 00:30:26,533
- I said sit.
- Right.

478
00:30:27,408 --> 00:30:28,367
Okay.

479
00:30:28,368 --> 00:30:31,037
Look. This is what you'll be doing, okay?

480
00:30:31,746 --> 00:30:34,039
Now, tonight... See these numbers?

481
00:30:34,040 --> 00:30:35,750
Send out a text to all of them.

482
00:30:36,417 --> 00:30:37,293
Got it?

483
00:30:37,877 --> 00:30:38,710
Yes.

484
00:30:38,711 --> 00:30:40,755
You look dumb as fuck.

485
00:30:41,256 --> 00:30:42,590
Goddamn it.

486
00:30:48,847 --> 00:30:50,932
TEXT RECIPIENT LIST

487
00:30:59,107 --> 00:31:00,441
IT'S BONG, I'VE BEEN TAKEN

488
00:31:02,986 --> 00:31:03,820
You're...

489
00:31:06,489 --> 00:31:08,408
We're all being watched here.

490
00:31:10,326 --> 00:31:12,119
They're watching our monitors too.

491
00:31:12,120 --> 00:31:14,581
Who the fuck is talking?

492
00:31:21,212 --> 00:31:23,589
Fucking hell. Look at me.

493
00:31:23,590 --> 00:31:26,801
You son of a bitch.
When did I say you could open your trap?

494
00:31:29,804 --> 00:31:32,807
You're fucking pissing me off,
you goddamn bastard.

495
00:31:34,559 --> 00:31:36,018
You fucking moron.

496
00:31:36,019 --> 00:31:37,769
Why don't you listen?

497
00:31:37,770 --> 00:31:38,979
You fucking bastard.

498
00:31:38,980 --> 00:31:42,692
Don't fucking act
like you're in pain, all right?

499
00:31:48,656 --> 00:31:49,698
50,000 WON BONUS

500
00:31:49,699 --> 00:31:51,199
MESSAGE HAS BEEN SENT

501
00:31:51,200 --> 00:31:54,786
Get the hell out, goddamn dumbasses.
You fucking morons.

502
00:31:54,787 --> 00:31:57,582
You're fucking useless.
I said get the hell out!

503
00:32:00,376 --> 00:32:02,712
Get back to work, you fuckers.

504
00:32:03,254 --> 00:32:05,255
- Damn it.
- What's the boss flipping over now?

505
00:32:05,256 --> 00:32:07,507
There's a problem
with the Cambodian server.

506
00:32:07,508 --> 00:32:10,969
I hear it's lagging
because of damn traffic spikes.

507
00:32:10,970 --> 00:32:13,431
- Damn complaint calls keep coming in.
- I know, fuck.

508
00:32:13,932 --> 00:32:16,809
- That's not on us.
- Why is he taking it out on us? Damn it.

509
00:32:19,354 --> 00:32:20,437
Are you asleep?

510
00:32:20,438 --> 00:32:23,357
Wow, I already feel like fucking shit,
and you're asleep.

511
00:32:23,358 --> 00:32:25,610
Fine, I'll make sure
you fucking stay asleep.

512
00:32:28,154 --> 00:32:30,073
Please!

513
00:32:30,573 --> 00:32:32,532
I'll put you to sleep forever, you fucker.

514
00:32:32,533 --> 00:32:34,451
Just a moment.

515
00:32:34,452 --> 00:32:37,205
I think I can do it.

516
00:32:38,414 --> 00:32:40,749
- Do what?
- The Cambodian server.

517
00:32:40,750 --> 00:32:44,169
I think you need to set up a reverse proxy
